          "type": "text",
          "text": "What will this TypeScript function return for n = 4?"
        },
        {
          "type": "code-block",
          "code": "function sumTo(n: number): number {\n  let sum = 0;\n  for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) sum += i;\n  return sum;\n}"
        }
      ],
      "options": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "code-line",
              "code": "6"
            }
          ],
          "isCorrect": false
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "code-line",
              "code": "10"
            }
          ],
          "isCorrect": true
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "code-line",
              "code": "16"
            }
          ],
          "isCorrect": false
        }
      ],
      "explanation": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function calculates the sum of integers from 1 to n. For n=4: 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 = 10. This is also known as the triangular number formula: n(n+1)/2."
        }
      ]
