          "text": "Pick the expression that creates an array with values 1, 2, 3 in JavaScript."
        }
      ],
      "options": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "code-line",
              "code": "[1, 2, 3]"
            }
          ],
          "isCorrect": true
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "code-line",
              "code": "{1, 2, 3}"
            }
          ],
          "isCorrect": false
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "code-line",
              "code": "(1, 2, 3)"
            }
          ],
          "isCorrect": false
        }
      ],
      "explanation": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Arrays in JavaScript use square brackets []. Curly braces {} define objects, and parentheses () are used for grouping expressions or function calls. The comma operator in (1, 2, 3) evaluates to just 3."
